# Capstone Git Workflow

- Use Conventional Commits (e.g., `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`).
- Never commit `node_modules/`.
- Ensure the README includes project setup instructions and `npm run dev`.
- Keep the project rules (`CLAUDE.md` or `.cursor/rules`) up to date.
- Before suggesting a commit message, ensure it follows the Conventional Commits specification.